2026-03-28 19:02:31,739 - groq._base_client - DEBUG - Request options: {'method': 'post', 'url': '/openai/v1/chat/completions', 'files': None, 'idempotency_key': 'stainless-python-retry-465d916a-0499-42b8-bd6e-60f9fb71e4c6', 'json_data': {'messages': [{'role': 'system', 'content': 'you are a doctor so only give me  information about medicine'}, {'role': 'user', 'content': 'what is microsoft\n'}, {'role': 'assistant', 'content': None, 'tool_calls': [{'type': 'function', 'id': '9w4qqx1rn', 'function': {'name': 'tavily_search_results_json', 'arguments': '{"query": "Microsoft medical technology"}'}}]}, {'role': 'tool', 'content': '[{"title": "Microsoft Healthcare: 5 Innovations in Healthcare Technology", "url": "https://www.incworx.com/blog/microsoft-healthcare-technology-innovations", "content": "Beyond pediatric research, Microsoft collaborates with partners like Adaptive Biotechnologies to advance understanding of complex diseases. Their joint work spans areas such as ovarian cancer, pancreatic cancer, autoimmune conditions, and more, demonstrating how AI and cloud technology are reshaping the future of medical discovery.\\n\\n## Learn About More Innovations in Microsoft Healthcare Technology\\n\\nAs digital transformation accelerates, technology is becoming an essential part of how healthcare organizations deliver care, communicate, and operate. The ability to share information securely and efficiently can directly influence patient outcomes, and Microsoft 365 continues to introduce tools that make healthcare safer, more connected, and more resilient. [...] AI\u2011powered assistants can analyze large volumes of clinical data, detect subtle abnormalities in imaging, and surface insights that might be difficult for humans to spot. Microsoft’s healthcare\u2011focused AI tools support this shift. Solutions like the Microsoft Healthcare Bot (now part of Azure Health Bot) provide symptom checking, triage support, and access to up\u2011to\u2011date medical information, helping clinicians make more informed decisions.\\n\\nMicrosoft is also investing heavily in AI\u2011driven medical research. Azure Genomics enables secure, scalable genomic analysis and accelerated sequencing workflows. These capabilities support major research institutions, including organizations that manage some of the world’s largest pediatric cancer genomics datasets. [...] Microsoft Teams now provides a secure foundation for clinical workflows. Care teams can build customizable processes, automate routine steps, and ensure the right information reaches the right person at the right time. Administrators can apply role\u2011based permissions to protect sensitive data, while each user can personalize their workspace so essential tools and apps are always within reach.\\n\\n## 4. An API for Fast Healthcare Interoperability Resources (FHIR)\\n\\nOne of the most impactful advancements in the Microsoft ecosystem for healthcare is the Azure API for FHIR. This modern, standards\u2011based API makes it easier to build and customize health data solutions that integrate seamlessly with existing systems.", "score": 0.99967754}, {"title": "Medical, health, and genomics - Microsoft Research", "url": "https://www.microsoft.com/en-us/research/research-area/medical-health-genomics/", "content": "The Health and Life Sciences (HLS) group at Microsoft is dedicated to advancing healthcare and life sciences through innovative technology solutions, fostering collaboration, and driving impactful research to improve patient outcomes and streamline healthcare operations.…\\n\\nTool \\n\\n### MIRA: Medical Time Series Foundation Model for Real-World Health Data\\n\\nMIRA is a foundation model for medical time-series, designed to learn a unified representation space across heterogeneous clinical datasets and support zero-shot forecasting in real-world healthcare settings. Unlike conventional time-series models that operate on fixed…\\n\\nCareer Opportunity \\n\\n### Technical Program Manager II\\n\\nLocation: Redmond, WA, US\\n\\nResearch Area(s): Artificial intelligence, Medical, health and genomics [...] Location: Redmond, WA, US\\n\\nResearch Area(s): Artificial intelligence, Human language technologies, Medical, health and genomics\\n\\nMicrosoft’s Health and Life Sciences (HLS) group is driving a healthcare revolution with AI-powered solutions like Dragon Copilot. These innovations empower healthcare professionals to enhance patient care, improve outcomes, boost productivity, and reduce burnout. Our…\\n\\nCareer Opportunity \\n\\n### Research Intern – Applied Speech Research\\n\\nLocation: Berkeley, CA, US; Burlington, MA, US\\n\\nResearch Area(s): Artificial intelligence, Human language technologies, Medical, health and genomics [...] Do you come alive when a path isn’t obvious? Would you see open, complex, scientific, AI/ML, and engineering problems as something to be shaped into clear plans, crisp milestones, and aligned teams? We’re Microsoft Research…\\n\\nMicrosoft Research Blog \\n\\n### UniRG: Scaling medical imaging report generation with multimodal reinforcement learning\\n\\n|  Sheng Zhang, Flora Liu, Guanghui Qin, Mu Wei, Hoifung Poon\\n\\nAI can help generate medical image reports, but today’s models struggle with varying reporting schemes. Learn how UniRG uses reinforcement learning to boost performance of medical vision-language models.\\n\\nThree white icons on a blue\u2011green gradient: a ribcage scan, a circuit\u2011style document, and a neural network diagram\\n\\nVideo \\n\\n### Microsoft Research India 2025 Highlights", "score": 0.9973061}, {"title": "Microsoft AI for better health", "url": "https://news.microsoft.com/health/", "content": "Microsoft \\n\\nSource\\n\\n0 Cart 0 items in shopping cart\\n\\nMicrosoft AI for better health\\n\\n# Microsoft AI for better health\\n\\nMicrosoft is shaping the next frontier of health AI innovation, providing resources, information and access to help media outlets, journalists and influencers bring their audiences along on the journey.\\n\\n## \\n\\nAt the intersection of medicine, biology and technology, Microsoft is helping to lead the health and life sciences transformation. By combining cutting-edge research and purpose-built AI, we’re reimagining every layer of the health tech stack and patient care. Working alongside patients, clinicians, researchers, our customers and the broader medical community, we’re unlocking new insights and accelerating the journey from scientific discovery to real-world impact. [...] Wolters Kluwer to integrate UpToDate into healthcare agent service in Microsoft Copilot Studio\\n Enhancing patient care with new AI solution for nurses\\n Paige’s cancer diagnostic Copilot, Alba, showcased by Microsoft at HLTH 2024 as transformative AI technology for healthcare\\n Mercy launches “Joy” chatbot to revolutionize employee benefits access [...] Atropos Health launches the Atropos Evidence Agent at Stanford Health Care and collaborates with Microsoft to improve evidence-based personalized medicine at the point of care\\n Lunit and Microsoft collaborate to advance AI-driven cancer diagnosis\\n Viome collaborates with Microsoft to deliver preventive healthcare with one of the world’s largest RNA datasets\\n Meritus uses AI to streamline, improve patient care\\n Kenvue announces 5-year collaboration with Microsoft to transform digital operations\\n Atostek ID is now compatible with Microsoft Azure Virtual Desktop\\n RAAPID joins Microsoft for Startups Pegasus Program with transactable marketplace offer\\n iCAD\u202fCollaborates with Microsoft to provide access to its mammography solutions in Microsoft’s Precision Imaging Network (PIN)", "score": 0.9961755}, {"title": "Microsoft Health Futures - Microsoft Research", "url": "https://www.microsoft.com/en-us/research/lab/microsoft-health-futures/", "content": "> Medicine, biology, and technology are rapidly converging. The future of health will be data-driven, predictive, and precise.\\n>\\n> Microsoft Health Futures is focused on empowering every person on the planet to live a healthier future. To this end, we are responsible for research, incubations, and moonshots that drive cross-company strategy, partnerships, and real-world impact across healthcare and the life sciences.\\n>\\n> We are a global, inclusive, and diverse crew of researchers, scientists, engineers, biotechnologists, designers, social scientists, strategists, healthcare experts, and medical professionals.\\n>\\n> We are always looking for passionate and talented individuals to join us. Check out our open positions or contact us for more info!\\n\\n## Featured research [...] # Microsoft Health Futures\\n\\n## Highlights\\n\\n### Microsoft Announces New Foundation Model For Digital Pathology, Diving Deeper Into Clinical Medicine\\n\\n### Artificial Intelligence and the Future of Healthcare and Biotech | Panel discussion\\n\\n### AI for Precision Health | Video\\n\\n### GigaPath: Whole-Slide Foundation Model for Digital Pathology", "score": 0.9942697}, {"title": "Healthcare Data and AI Solutions - Microsoft", "url": "https://www.microsoft.com/en-us/health-solutions/healthcare-data-ai", "content": "Unify healthcare data in solutions powered by AI to create a 360-degree view of patient health. Integration of this kind supports early disease detection, personalized treatment plans, risk assessments, and smarter chronic disease management—driving improvements in patient care, clinician experience, and operational performance.\\n\\n  A doctor and a nurse looking at a computer screen.\\n Use AI models in healthcare to analyze diverse data types—clinical notes, images, genomics, and more—without the need for extensive computational resources. This helps accelerate breakthroughs in pharmaceuticals, biotechnology, and clinical care, allowing organizations to build, customize, and deploy advanced solutions quickly and efficiently. [...] This is the Trace Id: c2e128522a11358d69693f55f58c6d6c   \\n\\n Microsoft \\n\\nHealth solutions\\n\\nHealth solutions\\n\\nHealth data and AI solutions\\n\\n# Simplify complex healthcare data\\n\\nAmplify the power of your healthcare data through trusted Azure infrastructure, advanced Microsoft Fabric analytical solutions, and powerful AI tools in Microsoft Foundry and Copilot Studio—backed by our ongoing commitment to innovation in Microsoft for Healthcare.\\n\\nRead the e-book\\n\\nOVERVIEW\\n\\n## Advance healthcare innovation through data and AI\\n\\nTransform healthcare with AI-powered data, empowering teams to deliver personalized care, streamline data management, and enhance patient experiences. [...] A doctor holding a tablet and talking on the phone.\\n Streamline administrative tasks, automate workflows, and provide clinicians and patients with vetted, reliable information using AI-powered healthcare agents. These agents improve operational efficiency, support clinical decision-making, and enhance patient engagement, all while maintaining high standards of safety, privacy, and regulatory compliance.", "score": 0.9932025}]', 'tool_call_id': '9w4qqx1rn'}], 'model': 'llama-3.3-70b-versatile', 'n': 1, 'reasoning_effort': None, 'reasoning_format': None, 'service_tier': 'on_demand', 'stop': None, 'stream': False, 'temperature': 0.7, 'tools': [{'type': 'function', 'function': {'name': 'tavily_search_results_json', 'description': 'A search engine optimized for comprehensive, accurate, and trusted results. Useful for when you need to answer questions about current events. Input should be a search query.', 'parameters': {'properties': {'query': {'description': 'search query to look up', 'type': 'string'}}, 'required': ['query'], 'type': 'object'}}}]}}
